  </p>

  <p>
    Some guardians place a small plant nearby (cat-safe varieties only) to bring
    life to the space. Others use a simple screen or furniture piece that provides
    visual privacy without trapping odors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Air circulation matters. Good ventilation prevents odor buildup far better
    than covered boxes or air fresheners. A space that breathes stays fresher
    naturally.
  </p>

  <h2>Mindful Maintenance</h2>

  <p>
    The ritual of scooping can become a moment of mindfulness rather than a chore.
