  </p>

  <p>
    Use gentle, unscented cleaners when you wash the box. Residual fragrances
    can deter cats from returning. Simple soap and water, followed by thorough
    drying, is often best.
  </p>

  <h2>Multiple Cat Considerations</h2>

  <p>
    The old rule suggests one litter box per cat, plus one extra. In a multi-cat
    home, this ensures every cat has options. Placement matters tooâ€”spread boxes
    throughout your home rather than clustering them.
  </p>

  <p>
    Some cats prefer their own designated box. Others share happily. Observe
    your cats' preferences and honor them. Conflict over litter box access
    can create lasting stress.
  </p>

